Parliament, Thursday, 9 March 2023 – The Portfolio Committee on Forestry, Fisheries and Environment will from tomorrow visit Gauteng Province to conduct public hearings on the Climate Change Bill. The Bill seeks to ensure the effective management of inevitable climate change impacts by enhancing adaptive capacity, strengthening resilience and reducing vulnerability to climate change, with a view to building social, economic and environmental resilience and adequate national adaptation response in the context of the global climate change response. The committee invites all interested citizens and organisations to attend the public hearings and comment on the Climate Change Bill. Details of the public hearings are as follows: Date: 10 March (Friday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: East Bank Hall (Alexandra) – City of Johannesburg Metropolitan Municipality  Date: 11 March (Saturday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: D H Williams Hall (Katlehong) – City of Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Municipality  Date: 12 March (Sunday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: Khutsong Community Hall (Carletonville) – Merafong Local Municipality  For media enquiries or interviews with the committee Chairperson, please contact: Name: Sakhile Mokoena Parliamentary Communication Services Cell: 081 705 2130 E-mail: smokoena@parliament.gov.za The Constitution says a parliamentary committee meeting may not be closed to the public “unless it is reasonable and justifiable to do so in an open and democratic society”. Democratic Alliance on the provincial list for the province of Eastern Cape